COMMAND LINE

To run the interactive command line:

  bin/repl


INSERT DATA

To insert test data into the system (note there is already test data at //test/path):

1. start the repl in one terminal

  bin/repl

2. in another terminal run

  bin/insert

Note: test data is inserted at the path //insert/test/path


RESET DATA

1. remove data directory

  rm -rf data/

2. start the repl in one terminal

  bin/repl

3. initalize the test dataset

  bin/init

4. exit the REPL
  
quirrel> :quit 
       | <ctrl-d>


EXAMPLE QUERIES

quirrel> count(dataset(//test/path))
       | <ctrl-d>

quirrel> tests := dataset(//test/path)
       | count(tests where tests.gender = "male")
       | <ctrl-d>

quirrel> tests := dataset(//test/path)
       | histogram('platform) :=
       |   { platform: 'platform, num: count(tests where tests.platform = 'platform) }
       | histogram
       | <ctrl-d>
